ZH: 蛇是一种爬行动物。
EN: Snakes are a type of reptile.

ZH: 这条蛇是有毒的。
EN: This snake is venomous.

ZH: 他在路上看到了一条蛇。
EN: He saw a snake on the road.

ZH: 蛇的眼睛看起来很奇怪。
EN: The snake's eyes look very strange.

ZH: 这条蛇在草丛中缠绕。
EN: The snake is coiled up in the grass.

ZH: 孩子们被吓坏了，因为有条蛇出现了。
EN: The children were terrified when they saw a snake.

ZH: 这种蛇的皮肤很光滑。
EN: This type of snake has smooth skin.

ZH: 警告：这个地区有毒蛇。
EN: Warning: There are venomous snakes in this area.

ZH: 蛇的舌头是黑色的。
EN: The snake's tongue is black.

ZH: 蛇蜕皮的时候会很活跃。
EN: Snakes are very active when shedding their skin.

ZH: 这种蛇的毒液非常致命。
EN: The venom of this snake is highly deadly.

ZH: 有些人会被看到蛇吓坏。
EN: Some people are terrified when they see a snake.

ZH: 这条蛇的身体上有美丽的斑纹。
EN: The snake's body has beautiful markings on it.

ZH: 印度眼镜蛇是最具攻击性的蛇之一。
EN: The Indian cobra is one of the most aggressive snakes.

ZH: 蛇是一个有着神秘象征意义的动物。
EN: Snakes are animals with mysterious symbolic meanings.

ZH: 这样的蛇在这个地区很常见。
EN: This type of snake is commonly found in this region.

ZH: 他在动物园里看到了很多种蛇。
EN: He saw many different kinds of snakes at the zoo.

ZH: 蛇是一种优秀的掠食者。
EN: Snakes are excellent predators.

ZH: 古代一些文明将蛇视为神圣的生物。
EN: Some ancient civilizations considered snakes to be sacred creatures.

ZH: 如果你不惹蛇，蛇也不会伤害你。
EN: Snakes will not harm you if you do not provoke them.
